HEADWORD: Substantiality
<hw>Sub*stan`ti*al"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
quality or state of being substantial; corporiety;
materiality.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The soul is a stranger to such gross
<qex>substantiality</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

